MALACAÑANG Manila

PROCLAMATION NO. 495

RESERVING FOR THE BUREAU OF FISHERIES AND AQUATIC RESOURCES AS SITE FOR THE FRESHWATER DEMONSTRATION FISH FARM PURPOSES UNDER THE ADMINISTRATION OF THE DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE A PARCEL OF LAND OF THE PUBLIC DOMAIN, LOCATED AT LIWAN WEST, RIZAL, KALINGA, ISLAND OF LUZON

Upon the recommendation of the Secretary of Environment and Natural Resources and by the powers vested in me by law, I, GLORIA MACAPAGAL-ARROYO , President of the Republic of the Philippines, do hereby reserve for the Bureau of Fisheries and Aquatic Resources (BFAR) under the administration of Department of Agriculture (DA) as site for Freshwater Demonstration Fish Farm purposes, subject to actual survey, and withdraw the same from occupation, entry, sale, lease or other disposition unless further declared as alienable and disposable by the President which parcel of land is more particularly describes as follows:

LOT NO. 5595-B, Csd-2-05-003852 (Equivalent to Lot No. 8330, Pls-245)

A parcel of land (Lot-5595-B, Csd-2-05-003852) situated at Liwan West, Rizal, Kalinga, Island of Luzon. Bounded on the W. and NW. along lines 1-2-3 by a road 10 meters wide; on the N. and NE. along lines 3-4-5-6 by a road 10 meters wide; on the E. and SE. along lines 6-7-8-9 also by a road 10 meters wide; on the S. along line 9-1 by Lot 5595-A, Csd-2-05-003852.

Beginning at a point marked “1” on plan being N. 31-41′ W., 354.41 m. from BLLM No. 41, Pls-245, Kalinga, thence;

199.14 m. to point 2;

14.82 m. to point 3;

31.30 m. to point 4;

14.14 m. to point 5;

119.88 m. to point 6;

10.41 m. to point 7;

120.97 m. to point 8;

21.27 m. to point 9;

160.03 m. to point of

beginning , containing an area of TWENTY NINE THOUSAND ONE HUNDRED EIGHTEEN (29,118) square meters, more or less. All points referred to are indicated on the plan and are marked on the ground by PS Cyl. Conc . 15×60 cms. Bearings: True; Date of survey: June 1, 1985; Executed by Engr. Ceferino B. Soriano and approved on July 16, 1985.

The tract of land herein reserved shall be non-alienable and shall not be subject to occupation, entry, sale, lease, or other disposition until again declared alienable by proclamation of the President.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF , I have hereunto set my hand and caused the seal of the Republic of the Philippines to be affixed.

DONE in the City of Manila, this 4 th day of November , in the year of Our Lord, Two Thousand and Three.

( Sgd .) GLORIA MACAPAGAL-ARROYO

By the President: ( Sgd .) ALBERTO G. ROMULO Executive Secretary

